0

With suitable parameter choices, both PDFs can achieve the the peaked distributions typical of
many CCTDs (Golubev, 2016) (see Fig 2). As special cases of the hypoexponential distributions,
these distributions also have the significant advantage that they can be simulated using the ubiquitous Gillespie stochastic simulation algorithm. This will allow for the appropriate representation
of CCTDs in stochastic models of cell populations, in contrast to the inappropriate exponentially
distributed times which are commonly used (Baar et al., 2016; Castellanos-Moreno et al., 2014;
Figueredo et al., 2014; Mort et al., 2016; Ryser et al., 2016; Turner et al., 2009; Zaider and Minerbo,

bioRxiv preprint first posted online May. 26, 2017; doi: http://dx.doi.org/10.1101/142521. The copyright holder for this preprint (which was
not peer-reviewed) is the author/funder. It is made available under a CC-BY-NC-ND 4.0 International license.

