Figure 2. Post-mitotic separation of daughter cells

827

Mitotic cells were tracked manually for 60 minutes prior to cytokinesis and daughters for a
further 120 minutes. Two types of mitotic types were revealed: (A) Daughter cells
positioned adjacent or (B) which separated after mitosis. Displayed are 3D projections (top
panels) and 2D sections through an organoid branch. Metaphase (green) and daughters
(red/blue) are highlighted. Representative tracks show the distance of the mitotic mother
(black line) and daughters (red/blue lines) from the original starting position. (P)rophase,
(M)etaphase, (C)ytokinesis, interkinetic nuclear migration (INM), and basal cell movement
(BM) are indicated. Distances between adjacently placed daughters (grey dashed line) are â¤
1 nuclear width (6Îźm) whereas distances between separating daughters is greater.

