(F) Individual frames of an H2B-GFP organoid stained with Mitotracker highlighting a mitotic
cell whose daughters separate shortly after mitosis. Time points reflecting metaphase,
cytokinesis and after return of daughters to their interphase position (reinsertion) are
shown. A line-intensity profile was generated between marked daughters (A and B) during
cytokinesis and after âinsertionâ. After reinsertion, a discrete H2B-GFP peak was detected
that correspond to the neighbouring cell that displaces the two daughters (red arrow). The
neighbouring cell has two distinct Mitotracker peaks on either side of its H2B-GFP signal
(black arrows).

