divisions where all daughter cells are placed adjacent to each other (i.e. đ = 0 for all
divisions) and for a heterogeneous population (right) of cell divisions where đ = 0 for two
thirds of divisions (red) and đ = 1 for the remaining third (blue). Constant fits to these
distributions (using data for all ages) are denoted by dotted lines.

